<br>
One thing India has a definte advantage is information to its public. India is a democracy. Pakistan is a joke of a democracy, with military ruling most of its years. Regarding China, its communist...need i say more ?<br>
i have an american friend who lives in shanghai and she cant even access normal sites on google, let alone controversial sites. I even know a chinese friend, rather close one, who has immigrated from mainland china 3-4 years ago.. she is 20 now and even she wasnt aware of the horrors of the Tianenmen square before she looked it up in Canada. Chances are that the average indian picture of the events are more accurate than the average chinese. <br>
On that note, it must be said that propraganda is avery strong morale force during a war. Given the relatively high mis-information to the chinese populace compared to India's, Chinese forces are likely to be more motivated than India's.<br>
<br>
Now the historical info:<br>
India has NEVER attacked any land beyond the Hindu-Kush mountains in afghanistan where as foreign forces have come streaming into India since 1000AD or something. Why did they come ? Partly because of India's grandure of wealth and culture and partly because Indian socio-structure is more tolerent to foreigners than chinese ( as in if you came to india, you would be considered an Indian long before likewise in China. Reason i know this is because i travelled both countries). Why hasnt india attacked anyone beyond the hindu-kush ? <br>
Simple. Geographic constraints. You dont expect a medival force of marching soldiers and horses to show tremendous interest to cross a few hundred, if not thousand kilometres of one of the highest and harshest mountain system in the world simply to occupy a quasi-desert ( central asia) or a land which is around the same level of richness in natural resources( East China).It may be noted that while china has larger natural resources, it is almost twice the size of India and per square mile, India comes out on top. With proper utilization of both countries resources, the natural resource/economic aspect of the war would be very close and evenly balanced. That being said, the indian psyche is much more geared towards peaceful negotiations than Chinese. If this wern't so, India would have attacked pakistan long before both nations had nukes and if not beat pakistan ( tough to do with china around, but i am sure diplomatic gaps existed in the last 50 years to keep china busy somewhere else) atleast hurt them a lot. The most populous pakistani belt is around karachi and lahore and they are not more than a day or two's march from the indian border. <br>
<br>
Now, let me address the military situation.<br>
China has to cross the himalayas, to have a ground presence in india ( something quiete impossible.... forget the indian army,some of the passes in the himalayas could be held up by a few grannies weilding brooms.) The himalayas have been the hardest to conquer for any invading force and even the mighty british army was nearly humbled by local nepalese farmers during the colonial era. So simply speaking, that wont happen. Even if one or the other country could get a logistically possible way to terran-invade the other, the simple population equity says control will never be held by either side. <br>
<br>
Now, Indian navy is a lot more mobile than China's and bear in mind that a significant of Chinese navy is kept reserved for any potential trouble in the taiwan-south korea-japan area. They would be called off only if the chinese navy was facing gravest of losses. This leaves the entire Indian navy, which is much more mobile due to non-existant pakistani navy, to virtually engage and even defeat the south china sea presence of chinese navy. <br>
<br>
Now we come to the ariel attack scenario. India has superior interceptors than chinese but lack the range to do damage to east-china.This means that while chinese air force  will be very mildly successful in getting through the indian interceptor range, it simply wouldnt be worth the effort and certainly not the losses it would suffer. ( i personally give 1 in 20 chance for a chinese fighter to elude the indian interceptor net and come close to bombing vital indian locations. So, while the naval battle favours india, the air battle is pretty much a stalemate.<br>
<br>
Lastly, ICBMs.<br>
India has a range that can reach only the fringes of eastern china. While this will not cause a dramatic chinese civillian casualty figure, bear in mind that the regions immediately east and north of tibet are vulnerable to indian missiles and thats where the bulk of chinse ground force base and command centers are. <br>
China can, ofcourse, hit any indian city if it wants and that is a major advantage china has.However, Indians are putting considerable efforts into researching missiles that reach eastern china. Given that India has a strong scientific community and lots of highly educated folks,( i think india is the only asian nation to have nobel lauriates in phys/chem/bio/economics who did their work in india) i think that it would be a matter or time and india can even the missile table. When that happens, it will be a minor cold war like russia-USA. neither can survive the attack and whoever is the 'conventional ' victor, will be the human equivalent of a quadruplegic. However, when that happens, it would leave pakistan in a very precarious position, since given the geography, India could potentially 'storm' pakistan and with adequate preparation, destroy its missiles while at ground. Once,that happens ( logistically impossible now, possible but difficult in the future) pakistan is in deep trouble.<br>
<br>
Now, grow up, stop calling chinese chinks, indians stupid farmers and pakis eviel. Go get laid or something<br>
